content: Overrepresented transcription factor binding sites (TFBSs) for each cluster were predicted using Transcription Factor Matrix (TFM) Explorer (see methods for scanning parameters). Identified TFBSs are given with their rank (most significant first); matrix name; transcription factor name; information of content of the matrix; gc content of the matrix (G+C)%; location of the identified binding sites (relative to TSS); and p-value. For each identified TFBS the entire list of hits in all input sequences is also given, Information includes gene name; location (position and strand orientation) of binding motif; matrix similarity; and motif instance.
